            Use the idea of cut sets/points to explain why the unit circle in <m>\R^2</m> is not homeomorphic to the interval <m>[0,1]</m> in <m>\R</m>.
            Note: the unit circle is the set <m>\{(x,y) \mid x^2+y^2 = 1\}</m>.
